# SockPuppet Release

The zip file contains the minimal code needed to:

1. prepare the wiki-socks dataset
2. train AD-GNN on wiki-socks
3. test on the Raszewski dataset with:
   - zero-shot transfer
   - batched task-level evaluation

It does not include the datasets themselves.

Datasets
========

1. Wiki-Socks dataset
Download / repository:
https://github.com/lraszewski/wiki-socks

2. Raszewski et al. ACL 2025 sockpuppet investigations dataset
Paper:
https://aclanthology.org/2025.acl-long.1083/

Public release source referenced by the paper:
https://github.com/lraszewski/wiki-socks

Notes
=====

- The release code expects the wiki-socks raw CSV files under:
  data/wiki-socks-data/data/

- The Raszewski evaluation code expects:
  data/raszewski_dataset/data/
  data/raszewski_dataset/stats.csv


## Folder Layout

- `scripts/convert_wikisocks_data.py`: convert raw wiki-socks investigations into one activity log plus labels
- `scripts/build_windows.py`: build temporal windows from the activity log
- `scripts/train_adgnn.py`: train AD-GNN on wiki-socks windows
- `scripts/evaluate_on_raszewski_fast.py`: zero-shot transfer to Raszewski using the trained checkpoint
- `scripts/prepare_raszewski_cache.py`: optional preprocessing for batched Raszewski evaluation
- `scripts/evaluate_on_raszewski_batched.py`: batched Raszewski evaluation
- `configs/default.yaml`: default windowing configuration

## Requirements

Install from inside `release/`:

```bash
pip install -e .
```

Main dependencies used by the released code:

- `pandas`
- `numpy`
- `scipy`
- `scikit-learn`
- `pyarrow`
- `pyyaml`
- `torch`
- `torch-geometric`
- `tqdm`

## Expected Data Layout

The commands below assume the following dataset locations relative to `release/`:

```text
data/
  wiki-socks-data/
    data/
      *.csv
  raszewski_dataset/
    data/
      *.csv
    stats.csv
```

If your data is elsewhere, replace the paths in the commands.

## Dataset 1: Wiki-Socks

### Step 1. Convert the raw investigations

This reads the raw wiki-socks investigation CSV files and produces:

- one unified activity log
- one JSON file with positive sockpuppet groups

Command:

```bash
python scripts/convert_wikisocks_data.py \
  --data-dir data/wiki-socks-data/data \
  --output-log data/raw/wikisocks_activity_log.csv \
  --output-labels data/wikisocks_labels.json
```

Outputs:

- `data/raw/wikisocks_activity_log.csv`
- `data/wikisocks_labels.json`

### Step 2. Build temporal windows

This slices the activity log into overlapping windows used by AD-GNN training.

Command:

```bash
python scripts/build_windows.py \
  --input data/raw/wikisocks_activity_log.csv \
  --config configs/default.yaml \
  --output data/processed/windows
```

Outputs:

- `data/processed/windows/window_*.parquet`
- `data/processed/windows/windows_metadata.csv`

### Step 3. Train AD-GNN on wiki-socks

This is the actual wiki-socks AD-GNN training script used for the release.

Command:

```bash
python scripts/train_adgnn.py \
  --windows data/processed/windows \
  --labels data/wikisocks_labels.json \
  --output results/positive_all/adgnn
```

Important outputs:

- `results/positive_all/adgnn/config.json`
- `results/positive_all/adgnn/config.yaml`
- `results/positive_all/adgnn/summary.json`
- `results/positive_all/adgnn/best_model_global.pt`

The file `best_model_global.pt` is the checkpoint used by the zero-shot Raszewski script.

## Dataset 2: Raszewski

There are two evaluation modes in this release.

### Option A. Zero-Shot Transfer

This tests whether the wiki-socks-trained model transfers directly to Raszewski.

Run:

```bash
python scripts/evaluate_on_raszewski_fast.py \
  --model results/positive_all/adgnn/best_model_global.pt \
  --output results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_fast
```

Useful optional arguments:

- `--device cpu`
- `--device cuda`
- `--sample-size 1000`
- `--max-users 200`
- `--sort-by-size`
- `--coord-method sparse`
- `--coord-method exact`

Main outputs:

- `results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_fast/config.yaml`
- `results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_fast/zeroshot_results_sample_*.csv`
- `results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_fast/summary.json`

### Option B. Batched Raszewski Evaluation

This script trains and evaluates on Raszewski investigations in batched multi-task mode.

#### Step B1. Optional cache preparation

This precomputes graph/features payloads used by the batched evaluator.

Command:

```bash
python scripts/prepare_raszewski_cache.py \
  --cache-dir results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_batched/cache
```

Optional arguments:

- `--sample-size 1000`
- `--full`
- `--max-users 200`
- `--sort-by-size`
- `--coord-method sparse`
- `--coord-method exact`

This step is optional because the evaluator can build missing cache entries by itself.

#### Step B2. Run the batched evaluator

Command:

```bash
python scripts/evaluate_on_raszewski_batched.py \
  --output results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_batched
```

Useful optional arguments:

- `--device cpu`
- `--device cuda`
- `--sample-size 1000`
- `--full`
- `--meta-batch-size 8`
- `--epochs 5`
- `--neg-ratio 2.0`
- `--group-size 3`
- `--infer-batch-size 256`
- `--max-users 200`
- `--sort-by-size`
- `--coord-method sparse`
- `--coord-method exact`
- `--cache-dir results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_batched/cache`

Main outputs:

- `results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_batched/config.yaml`
- `results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_batched/batched_results.json`
- `results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_batched/summary.json`

## Minimal End-to-End Sequence

If you want the shortest complete sequence:

```bash
pip install -e .

python scripts/convert_wikisocks_data.py \
  --data-dir data/wiki-socks-data/data \
  --output-log data/raw/wikisocks_activity_log.csv \
  --output-labels data/wikisocks_labels.json

python scripts/build_windows.py \
  --input data/raw/wikisocks_activity_log.csv \
  --config configs/default.yaml \
  --output data/processed/windows

python scripts/train_adgnn.py \
  --windows data/processed/windows \
  --labels data/wikisocks_labels.json \
  --output results/positive_all/adgnn

python scripts/evaluate_on_raszewski_fast.py \
  --model results/positive_all/adgnn/best_model_global.pt \
  --output results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_fast

python scripts/evaluate_on_raszewski_batched.py \
  --output results/raszewski/adgnn_eval_batched


